      "writtenOn": "2019-01-17T21:11:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why have validation here, vs relying on the service itself to do the validation? I fear the eventual discrepancy, which adds a new failure mode: passes internal verification but fails when doing the RPC.\n\nIn particular, Swarming\u0027s API has a way to validate that a task request is good or not.",
      "revId": "0b456e4e38662be30ca8e68a3d90c02a297112d4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3e506241_80be1003",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/lib/swarming.star",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-17T23:24:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Some validation is required, just to check types and overall structure of arguments, just to be able to generate protos.\n\nI agree that strict validation is probably overkill and it is often hard to decide what to validate here and what should be validated by the server. I\u0027ll remove over specific validation in a separate CL.",
